Package: d3tm
Title: A Zoomable Treemap Capable of Handling Unbalanced Hierarchical Data
Version: 0.3.1
Authors@R: c(person("Luke", "Heley", role = c("aut", "cre"),
                     email = "lajh87@me.com"))
Description: The treemap above uses interaction to reveal the hierarchy 
    incrementally: clicking on a node zooms in. Only two levels of the hierarchy 
    are visible at a time. This allows the layoutâ€™s aspect ratio to be optimized 
    for the current view, rather than computing a global layout. 
    It also allows the exploration of arbitrarily-large datasets: 
    data can be lazily-loaded and positioned on zoom.
